main event: Four elliptical-shaped objects emitting a bright yellow glow were observed flying over Bethesda, Maryland on June 22, 1955.
interesting points: The objects were observed for approximately 20 seconds by a ground-visual witness using 7-power binoculars.
The objects were estimated to be flying at an altitude of around 40,000 feet.
The objects were observed moving from northeast to west with no discernible details or trails.
There were no sounds associated with the objects.
The report states that there were aircraft reported in the area at the time, and that the objects could potentially have been those aircraft due to the limited information available.

photographs: Yes, the report indicates that photographs were taken, but they are not included in the provided documentation.
